platform.writeup:
As the streaming home of FX, Hulu has the privilege of hosting buzzy programming like Atlanta, AHS: NYC, and Welcome to Wrexhamon top of its original series (the ongoing Ramy and The Handmaids Tale) and stray hits from ABC (Abbott Elementary). Its depth is perhaps unrivaled in the streaming landscape. But a team full of role players cant compete with MVPs, and thats what HBO Max, Prime Video, and Disney+ have. House of the Dragon, The Rings of Power, and Andor took over the fall '22 slate, sucking all attention toward them like a streaming TV black hole. Hulu didn't falter, per se, but it also didn't make much of a statement.

This all while the streamer has raised prices: On October 10, Hulu began charging a dollar more per month for its ad-supported and $2 more for non-ad plans. That might not seem like a lot, but the costs add up when it comes to paying for a service that doesnt have one of the biggest shows of the season. Andrew Gruttadaro

platform.title: Apple TV+
platform.subtitle: Slow and steady wins the race for Apple TV+.
platform.writeup: Over the past couple of months, Apple TV+ has quietly continued to establish itself as one of the more reliable sources of consistent, high-quality content. Following a sudden price hike and a relative shortage of new content back in October, it looked like the prestige streamer might suffer a hit in the Streaming Wars. But early in 2023, Apple TV+ continues to hold its own against much bigger competitors like Prime and Disney+. This gradual surge is due in large part to a pair of returning shows, Mythic Quest and Slow Horses, two critically-touted series that follow weekly release schedules that allow for a constant output to subscribers as well as a steady stream of internet buzz. Theres no hiding the fact that the service has benefited greatly from an end-of-the-year content drought and a lack of significant titles from the streaming big guns, but its still finding success nonetheless. Apple TV+ will look to keep its steady momentum going and stick to its philosophy of quality over quantity with the premiere of Shrinking in late January, a new comedy series starring Harrison Ford and Jason Segel, who created the show with Ted Lassos Brett Goldstein. Kai Grady

platform.title: Paramount+
platform.subtitle: Is it too little too late for Paramount+?
platform.writeup: Its not that Paramount+ has nothing to offer: The streamer is a showcase for CBS hits, '90s artifacts and reality trash/gold from MTV, Comedy Centrals deep roster of underrated sitcoms, and classic movies from studios like Paramount Pictures, Sony Pictures, and MGM. The service also now airs (or holds hostage, depending on who you ask) the UEFA Champions League. But Paramount+ entered the Streaming Wars after the launches of Apple TV+, Disney+, HBO Max, and Peacockeven if it technically predated all of those services as CBS All Accessand taking attention away from any of them has been a Sisyphean task ever since. The subscriber base (of 40 million) is strong enough that it has to be in the conversation, but until Paramount+ has its Severance, its going to remain a streaming afterthought. Andrew Gruttadaro

Amazon spent a billion dollars to bring Lord of the Rings to streaming TVand it probably doesnt regret a single penny. The Rings of Power earned 1.3 billion viewing minutes in just its first few days of release, according to Nielsen, a number that topped House of the Dragons total. Perhaps even more importantly, fans of J.R.R. Tolkien arent making a citizens arrest of Jeff Bezos for his crimes against IP: The series may not be beloved by all, but it is nowhere near the disaster it couldve been. Season 2 is already in production and could be out by this time next year.

But a funny thing happens when you spend that much money on one show: You dont have all that much left over for the rest of the slate. Prime didnt have much to hang its hat on in 2022 preRings of Power, and that was the case once again towards the end of the year. The Chlo Grace Moretzstarring, Jonathan Nolan and Lisa Joyproduced sci-fi series The Peripheral didn't command the viewership and buzz of Rings of Power; neither did the Emily Blunt Western The English. Amazon bet on Lord of the Rings to announce itself as a serious player in the Streaming Wars and to wrest attention away from Netflix and HBO. That was successful, but only partiallyin the middle of The Rings of Powers run, Netflix still released one of its most-watched shows ever while HBO reignited the Game of Thrones brand. And now comes a potentially bigger test, to see whether the in-roads made by Primes biggest series ever will remain paved while its off the air. Andrew Gruttadaro
platform.subtitle: The Rings of Power was a hit for Prime Video. What happens next?
platform.title: Prime

platform.writeup: Unexpected cancellations and head-scratching removals notwithstanding, HBO is on a huge win streak right now. Since late August of last year, the highly coveted Sunday-night time slot has been home to a trio of uber-popular prestige dramas. The record-breaking House of the Dragon, the viral The White Lotus, and as of January 15, the victory lap that is The Last of Us. The new hour-long HBO drama, based on the video game of the same name, is already breaking records: The shows premiere attracted 4.7 million viewers, which is the second-largest series debut for HBO in the last 13 years. In addition to having the first streaming hit of the new year, HBO Max showed up and showed out at the first award show of 2023, the Golden Globes, where it led all streamers in both wins and nominations (via HBO) and took home a total of four trophies, including Dragons win for Best Drama Series. The once longtime leader in our Streaming Wars rankings is finally back on top for the first time since mid-October. Buckle up for the next few months because HBOs got another hit on its hands. Kai Grady
platform.subtitle: HBO Max is inevitable.
platform.title: HBO Max
Netflix
platform.writeup: 2022 was a roller-coaster year for Netflix packed with all-time highs and all-time lows. But after outperforming its own subscriber forecastNetflix had expected to have its lowest fourth quarter in almost a decadeand adding more than 7.5 million subscribers during Q4 of 2022, it ended the year on a positive note on the backs of a trio of hugely successful originals (Monster, Wednesday, and Glass Onion) and the rollout of its cheaper, ad-supported plan. Netflix has yet to have a major hit since Wednesday debuted back in late November, but that doesnt mean its receded. It currently occupies 40 percent of our Weekly Top 10 list and remains at no. 2 on our Streaming Wars rankings despite a slow couple of months. As for the immediate future of the company, thats a little more uncertain. Last week, Netflix cofounder Reed Hastings resigned as co-CEO after close to 30 years at the company. And in the most recent earnings call, the newly promoted co-CEO, Greg Peters, announced that Netflixs plan to restrict account sharing will go into effect by the end of Q1 of 2023, and that they expect a wave of cancellations in response. Kai Grady
platform.subtitle: Netflix rebounded. Now the crackdown begins.

platform.title: Peacock
platform.writeup: Despite generating a little buzz during the World Cup, Peacock still hasn't produced any breakthrough originals and continues to struggle to curate content that creates mainstream demand. Since September, Peacock has gained an additional 3 million paid subscribers, pushing the streamers total number just past 18 million, with its high point coming in mid-December when it secured a Nielsen Top 10 placement thanks to the unlikely pairing of Yellowstone (seasons 1-4) and the streaming debut of Jordan Peeles Nope. Neither of those are Peacock originals, though, which gets at the larger issue: NBCUniversals streaming service isnt doing nearly enough to stand out from the crowd of otherfrankly, betteroptions. Peacock still lacks a flagship series and has yet to develop an easily understood brand identity. Theres still time to shift the narrative, especially with the upcoming debut of Rian Johnsons Poker Face, a 10-part mystery series starring Natasha Lyonne. But the clock is definitely ticking. Kai Grady
platform.subtitle: New year, same Peacock?

platform.writeup: What's surprising is how abrupt the transition will beand whos taking (back) the reins. The board has concluded that as Disney embarks on an increasingly complex period of industry transformation, board president Susan Arnold wrote in a statement, Bob Iger is uniquely situated to lead the company through this pivotal period. There remain many open questions. What exact chain of events led Iger to commit to a course of action he once called ridiculous? Will Iger unwind Chapeks controversial corporate shuffle, which took control of content distribution away from creative executives? Will he bring back longtime deputies like the formidable comms czar Zenia Mucha? Does Iger have one last blockbuster deal up his sleevesomething on par with the Marvel pact, to bring Disney into a new era? Iger may be a known quantity, but his sudden return puts Disney on uncertain ground, a twist worthy of its own blockbusters. Alison Herman

shows.title: Silicon Valley
shows.writeup: One of Silicon Valleys main comic engines has been the contrast between the overnight-success myth the Valley loves to propagatethe best ideas will rise to the top, and quicklyand the maddening drudgery of actually getting a company off the ground. (Or, as an investor in the fourth season premiere puts it: Really? Is it hard to become a billionaire? Welcome to the Valley, assholes.) Pied Piper isnt an unstoppable juggernaut. Its a delicate flower, one that could easily be crushed by a frivolous lawsuit, or a profit-minded executive, or a user-unfriendly interface that drives its own employees to fraud. The shows trajectory, or lack thereof, is also a way of fitting an ostensibly serialized comedy into the rhythms of a sitcom, where the status quo is sacred. Alison Herman

shows.title: Star Wars: The Clone Wars
shows.writeup: Set before the fall of the Jedi and the Republic, Clone Wars gives a good look at the politics surrounding the Republic, the precursor to the Empire.

shows.title: The Patient
shows.writeup: The Patient, a new FX limited series streaming weekly on Hulu, takes on a pairing of a different sort: that of a therapist and his you get the drift. Therapy has had something of a moment on TV lately, between the revival of In Treatment on HBO and Apple TV+s adaptation of The Shrink Next Door. (The moment isnt quite over; Shrinking, starring Jason Segel, entered production earlier this year.) These prior shows had their own flashy twists: Uzo Adubas doctor struggled with addiction and boundaries, while The Shrink Next Door told the true story of Dr. Ike Herschkopf, who all but took over his charges life. But The Patient takes onscreen therapy to new extremes. Dr. Alan Strauss (Steve Carell) lives a relatively normal lifeuntil hes kidnapped by Sam (Domhnall Gleeson), who cant reveal his true conflict until Alan is in captivity. Sam is a serial killer, and he wants Dr. Strauss to help cure him. Alison Herman

shows.title: The Town
shows.writeup: Ben Affleck grew up in Cambridge, only a few miles away from Charlestown, but to him the distance between the two places felt vast. Unfair or not, Charlestown had a reputation. It was like a different world, the actor and filmmaker says. When I was a kid, I was scared to go there. Violence, unsolved murders ... The story appealed to Affleck. A decade after establishing his Boston bona fides by cowriting and appearing in Good Will Hunting with Matt Damon, he was offered a chance to adapt the novel Prince of Thieves for the screen. It was concealing a character-based drama centered around themes that I was interested in, particularly the theme of children paying for the sins of their parents, Affleck says. But wrapping that in the sort of candy shell of a heist movie. Alan Siegel

shows.title: Survivor 43
shows.writeup: Whether youre just starting your Survivor journey or youre an Outwit, Outplay, Outlast veteran, you need to see Season 43 unfold. Out of the gates, casting has upped the ante with an incredibly diverse ensemble that has already proved to be especially easy to root for. A paralympian? A former gang member turned UC Berkeley graduate? A Peruvian immigrant who came out to his family only to be disowned and forced into houselessness? With all of these gems, we might actually need a villain to emerge. Amelia Wedemeyer
Taking a cue from the Bravo playbook, Selling Sunset gives us aspirational lifestyles and high-quality petty drama from model-looking cast members.
shows.title: Selling Sunset
Derry Girls
shows.writeup: A comedy about five wains (that means kids)Erin, Clare, Michelle, Orla, and Jamesand their eccentric relatives in Londonderry, Northern Ireland, in the 1990s. The kids attend an all-girls Catholic school (yes, even poor James); the parents banter incessantly while never seeming to work. Theres a baby who shows up every now and again, all cute and innocent, but is otherwise hardly ever mentioned. This show is incredibly funny, patently ridiculous, and, at times, unexpectedly moving. And if that wasnt already enough to convince you to check it out, the accents are amazing. Jack McCluskey

While the movie is set well after Andor, much of Andor's plot and motivation will set up the original Star Wars movie, including how the Rebel Alliance goes from underground network to full-blown resistance.
shows.title: Star Wars: Episode IV  A New Hope
Harry & Meghan
shows.writeup: On January 8, 2020, Prince Harry, the Duke of Sussex and sixth in the line of succession to the British throne, and his wife Meghan Markle stepped down as senior members of the royal family and moved to the United States. On March 7, 2021, Harry and Meghan explained their decision to Oprah Winfrey, alleging a pattern of racism and abuse that the royal apparatus not only chose not to protect the couple from, but perpetrated itself. Netflixs Harry & Meghan, a six-episode miniseries being released in two parts on Dec. 8 and 15, is the continuation of this story, the biggest in 21st century royal news. From the day they relinquished their titles on, Harry and Meghan have been at the center of a mudslinging labyrinth of reports, allegations, and tabloid headlines. According to them, this miniseries is an opportunity to see the truth, from the beginning of their relationship to today. No one knows the full truth, Harry says in the series trailer. We know the full truth. Andrew Gruttadaro

shows.title: Survivor: Heroes vs. Villains
shows.writeup: One of the best all-star seasons of any reality series, Heroes vs. Villains features a cast filled with returning players labeled based on their previous Survivor performance. Interestingly enough, you might find yourself laughing at the sheer stupidity of the Heroes tribe throughout this season, but most likely youll also fall in love with, or at least come to respect, a couple of villains who serve to remind us why labels are really just a matter of perspective.

The wilder sister (if thats even possible) to Love Is Blind, The Ultimatums premise is exactly what you think it is: A group of couples gather together in a fancy hotel in hopes of either getting engaged or moving on from the relationship. However, the twist in this series is that the couples who come together are split apart and then paired up with someone else in the hopes of gaining clarity on their own relationship or finding a new connection with the person they must live with for three weeks. Yes, that happens. And yes, chaos ensues. Amelia Wedemeyer
shows.title: The Ultimatum: Marry or Move On
FBoy Island
shows.writeup: It might be September now, but you can extend summer with a dating show thats up front (at least to the viewers) about contestants pastsand maybe presents?

shows.title: Cliffhanger
shows.writeup: In the late 80s and early 90s Sylvester Stallone had a simple formula: Hed be a guy who kicks some assthe only thing thatd change was his profession. In 1985 he was a boxer who kicked some ass in the Soviet Union; in 1987 he was a truck driver who kicked some ass via arm wrestling; and in 1993 he was a mountain climber who kicked some ass after becoming embroiled in a heist of a U.S. Treasury aircraft. Cliffhanger is a quintessentially absurd early-90s action movie (that also premiered at Cannes), and I mean that in the most delightful way possible. Come for Sly kicking ass; stay for the presupposition that John Lithgow can hang with him in a physical fight. Andrew Gruttadaro

In Jordan Peeles thriller Nope, the ratio of inspiration to perspiration is more balanced, and the directorial flexing is more impressive. Shot in IMAX by the gifted Dutch cinematographer Hoyte van Hoytema, on loan from Christopher Nolan and the James Bond franchise, Peeles third feature is a hugely scaled piece of work boasting the kind of swooping, Gods-eye camerawork available only to brand-name auteurs. Nope has a broader, more spectacular scope than either of its predecessors, and more obviously crowd-pleasing elements, as well. Whether or not Peele is The New Hitchcockan outrageous comparison he humorously downplayed in 2019 by referring to the Master of Suspense as a creephes cultivating a similarly sinister sense of showmanship. Each sequence has been carefully and effectively designed to make viewers either laugh, wince, or gleefully suspend their own disbelief. Adam Nayman
shows.title: Nope

shows.writeup: What We Do in the Shadows is adapted from the beloved 2014 feature-length film of the same name, which was written and directed by Flight of the Conchords cocreator Jemaine Clement and fellow New Zealandbased filmmaker and comedian Taika Waititi. The movie version is populated by a different set of vampires, and is set in Wellington rather than Staten Island, but otherwise Clement and Waititis televised adaptation is largely the same. Why are vampires being followed by a film crew? Well, why not? Doesnt everybody get their own documentary these days? The results are a bit like Parks and Recreation by way of Sartres No Exit. Elizabeth Nelson
shows.title: What We Do in the Shadows

shows.writeup: Besides being a very funny riff on the myth of Mr. Rightand featuring Ben Afflecks best screen performance, notwithstanding his contemplative beard-growing in the coda to The TownGone Girl makes David Finchers idea of one-way-or-another literal by telling its story through two competing viewpoints. Theres the view of Nick, a shitty husband and worse magazine writer who becomes a modern analog to one of Hitchcocks wrong men, and also that of Amy (Rosamund Pike), his wife who disappears mysteriously from their Missouri town and whose perspective on events serves variously to obscure, explain, and complicate the films story line. Adam Nayman
shows.title: Gone Girl
The Sandman
shows.writeup: After watching the episodes that make up the shows first season, its easy to understand why The Sandman took so long to get made. Given the comics mix of settings spanning dreams and the waking world, along with a story that features a number of eternal, anthropomorphic beings, demons, and nightmares, re-creating the original visuals in live action was a tremendous challenge. Just by existing, Netflixs The Sandman has achieved what once seemed unachievable, and the first season showcases the series potential. Daniel Chin

Thanksgiving is all about reflecting on what youre thankful forwhich, in this case, is not being any of the disgraced sports people featured in this anthology series. If you enjoyed Netflixs Manti Teo documentary, Bad Sports six episodes exploring true-crime sports scandalsaccompanied by gripping firsthand accounts and found footagewill hit just as hard. Touching on everything from the 1994 Arizona State basketball point-shaving scandal to the 2002 Winter Olympics pair-figure-skating controversy to the 2000 South Africa cricket match fixing, Bad Sport has plenty for sports fans, but also for the people who couldnt tell you what a triple axel is. Amelia Wedemeyer
shows.title: Bad Sport
Twin Peaks: Fire Walk With Me
shows.writeup: Everything youve heard about the movie isnt wrong: Fire Walk With Me, which opens a year and a week before Laura Palmers murder and then jumps ahead to document her final days, is a flawed film by definition, not least because of the oddly vestigial ties to the show Twin Peaks. You notice whats missing. The movie, with its gutted cast (no Lara Flynn Boyle! No Sherilyn Fenn!) and utter lack of whimsy, cant help but make you pine for more donut layouts and random crying fits from Officer Andy. But some part of meand not just the troll partfinds our collective inability to make heads or tails of the movie refreshing. K. Austin Collins

As a great philosopher once said, Dont Worry Darling is a movie that feels like a movielike a real, you know, go-to-the-theater film movie. And thats true. Dont Worry Darling is a movie that has characters and a plot; it has been written, directed, and produced; you can watch an edited and scored version of the footage that was filmed. Whether you enjoy that experience is a slightly more complicated question. So, it is here that I must ask you, darling: How do you feel about worrying? Jodi Walker
shows.title: Dont Worry Darling

shows.writeup: In the third season of Jack Ryan, the eponymous CIA analyst (John Krasinski) is in a race against time to stop Russian extremists from overthrowing the presidentnote: a fictional figure, not Vladimir Putinand setting off a chain of events that could lead to World War III. The setup is ridiculous, and thats part of the fun: The best Jack Ryan adaptations lean into the inherent absurdity of one mansomeone who, despite being a retired marine, feels more at home behind a deskbeing thrust into action for the sake of saving his country. Miles Surrey
shows.title: Tom Clancy's Jack Ryan
Point Break
shows.writeup: In Kathryn Bigelows 1991 classic Point Break, a group of devoted surfers dont simply refuse to take note of the Beach Closed signsthey seek them out, robbing Los Angeles banks to fund their daredevil world tour. Their motivations, however, seem loftier than financial freedom: Money is great, but have you ever, to quote one of these beach boys, had sex with gods? The surfers are looking to feel the ultimate rush. The goal isnt to go on holiday, but to make every day holya communion with nature, detached from a capitalist system. Yet Point Break lingers not primarily because of its anti establishment sentiment. As spiritual as the surfers it portrays are, Point Break remains, at the same time, a deeply silly movie. The very concept of bank-robbing surfer dudes is as ridiculous on paper as it is on the screen; it came from producer Rick King, who, while sitting on a beach, remembered an article hed read about Los Angeles being the bank robbery capital of the USA. Manuela Lazic

The pessimistic view of That 90s Show is that it could suffer a fate similar to the ill-fated That 80s Show, which was canceled after one season. But what That 90s Show has working in its favor is, above all else, nostalgia. (That 80s Show borrowed the original series format, but otherwise didnt have any crossover appeal.) The Forman household and other key locations in Point Place have been fastidiously recreated for That 90s Show, while the majority of the original castjoining Topher Grace and Laura Prepon are Mila Kunis, Ashton Kutcher, Wilmer Valderrama, Don Stark, and Tommy Chongreturn for cameos. (Unsurprisingly, Danny Mastersons Steven Hyde is excluded from the reunion.) Best of all, Kurtwood Smith and Debra Jo Rupp are back as series regulars; Red and Kitty have to balance giving their granddaughter independence without letting her get into too much trouble. Even after all these years, Red calling someone a dumbass or Kitty breaking out her distinctive laugh doesnt get old. Miles Surrey
shows.title: That '90s Show
Halloween
shows.writeup: Halloween kicked off a wave that redefined the horror genre, inspiring copycats and extremists, commercial juggernauts and crass exploitation pictures. It also inspired a steamer trunks worth of film theory, set a course for dozens of careers, and lit a torch for a future generation that would recontextualize and reinvent these films. Without Halloween, there is no Scream; without Scream, there is no Blumhouse. Sean Fennessey

You just know Adam Levine wishes he were still a judge on this show. Instead, the hit NBC series has added Camila Cabello as the newest celebrity chair-turner, wholl join John Legend and married couple Blake Shelton and Gwen Stefani. With the same music-competition format as the previous 21 seasons, its the sheer talent (and maybe the banter between coaches) that keep viewers coming back. Amelia Wedemeyer
shows.title: The Voice

shows.writeup: Kevin Bacon finally makes his MCU debut as himself?! Spend the holidays with everyone's favorite Guardians as Drax and Mantis try to cheer up Peter Quill on his favorite Terran holiday. Don't expect any major MCU implications from this one, but be on the lookout for some fun Easter eggs and advancements in Guardians of the Galaxy lore. Arjuna Ramgopal
shows.title: The Guardians of the Galaxy Holiday Special

shows.writeup: The setup: a group of terminally ill teens living in an old hospice to tell scary stories; terror, of course, ensues. The creators: Leah Fong and Mike Flanagan, the man behind previously superlative Netflix series The Haunting of Hill House and Midnight Mass. The payoff: Tremendous. The Midnight Club is yet another example of Flanagan and co. finding human stories within a deeply terrifying framework, a message to all doubters that horror can do more than just horrify. With Halloween fast approaching, the time is now to join the club. Andrew Gruttadaro
shows.title: The Midnight Club

shows.writeup:
But after a meeting with [Laura] Ziskin, [David Fincher] considered returning to Fox for Fight Clubso long as he could make it in the grandest way possible. I said, Heres the two ways you can go: you can do the $3 million version of this movie and make it on videotape and make your seditious little sharp stick in somebodys eye. But the real act of sedition, he told the studio, would be to invest tens of millions of dollars and to put movie stars in it and get people to go and talk about the anticonsumerist rantings of a schizophrenic madman. Brian Raftery

Fight Club is leaving Hulu on Nov. 30.
shows.title: Fight Club

shows.writeup: Among many things, Martin Scorseses Goodfellas is a movie about posing: posing as Sicilian; posing as a good Catholic, or a good Jew; posing as a good husband; posing as an innocent bystander; posing as a person with a conscienceand then later, posing as a person without a conscience; posing as someone who hasnt snorted an absurd amount of cocaine. Its a movie about faking it until you make it, but how the faking never stopseven after you have made it. We all tailor ourselves to certain standards, curtail our desires to whats appropriate, cage ourselves with moral codes. Henry wants to be a gangster because itll liberate him and allow him to do what he wants. But everyone has to do some things theyd rather not. Andrew Gruttadaro
shows.title: Goodfellas
We're All Going to the World's Fair
shows.writeup: A creepypasta-influenced debut feature from writer-director Jane Schoenbrun, this film feels like getting stuck in an internet rabbit hole. As scary and despairing as that sounds.

shows.title: The Ring
shows.writeup: Minor flaws aside, The Ring was still pretty much a model copy of an extraordinary foreign import, boasting a stellar lead performance by Naomi Watts (fresh off her triumph in Mulholland Drive), an appropriate amount of reverence for its source material, and a mesmerizing blue-steel color palette courtesy of director Gore Verbinski. A rare event: The decline in quality from the original to its Hollywood redux was surprisingly negligible. Adam Nayman

shows.title: The Many Saints of Newark
shows.writeup: At its best, Many Saints pulls at the thematic threads it shares with The Sopranos. Intrafamily violence and generational trauma haunt this world as much as those spirits haunt that graveyard. Everything in this cinematic universe is cyclical, and when David Chase et al. manage to connect back to The Sopranos in a way that complements the overarching story, it enriches both the film and the show. Justin Sayles

Its a rousing game of cat(fish) and mouse when isolated individuals come together virtually on the eponymous social media platform created specifically for this social experiment. Come here for high-volume lying.
shows.title: The Circle
Yellowstone
shows.writeup: Yellowstone is the story of the mighty and doomed Dutton family, with Kevin Costners sensibly dressed John Dutton at the helm. The clan has owned a sprawling cattle ranch in Montanas Paradise Valley called Yellowstone Ranch for generation upon generation, and the Duttons now find themselves in a position that their manifest destinyspouting ancestors were once on the other side of: trying to prevent others from taking their land. In Yellowstone, there are dead brothers and dead mothers, corrupt politicians and devious fly fishermen, indentured cowboys and feral horses. There are plans for the property that range from a casino to a ski resort, from a land grab to an airport. There are siblingsnamely Jamie, Kayce, and Beth Duttonwho alternately jostle over and scoff at their birthright and the dark, deadly forces required to preserve it. Katie Baker

Claire Denis modern update of Denis Johnsons story of lust and fear at the edge of revolution in Central America is one of the most desperate and gorgeous movies of 2022.

Streaming now on VOD. Arrives on Hulu on October 28.
shows.title: Stars at Noon

shows.writeup: Would you like to feel alive? Would you like to feel the blood simmer in your veins, and every synapse in your brain light up like Clark Griswolds house on Christmas Day? Would you care to fill your body with sweet, sweet serotonin, and flood your Twitter drafts with exclamation points? Then might I recommend The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City. Jodi Walker
shows.title: The Real Housewives of Salt Lake City
Rogue One: A Star Wars Story
shows.writeup: Cassian Andors introduction to the Star Wars universe, this movie provides pivotal context into the titular character as well as the state of the rebels well see in the show.

shows.title: The Bachelorette
shows.writeup: Season 19 of The Bachelorette is like a party where everyone else thought the other person was bringing ice, and now all the mezcal margaritas are lukewarm, and everyone is crying because they accidentally fell in love with the same Zak. The Bachelorette producers looked the audiences skepticism about two Bachelorettes dead in the eyes and said, Bet. They looked the very same two Bachelorettes in the eyes (framed by their newly adhered lash extensions and freshly laminated eyebrows), and said, Youre in charge. Jodi Walker

shows.title: Licorice Pizza
shows.writeup: There are times when Licorice Pizza almost feels like a highlight reel of Paul Thomas Andersons greatest tropes and momentsa victory lap around home turf. The dateline places it chronologically between Inherent Vice and Boogie Nights, which is also a pretty good description of its tone: warm, nostalgic, and only faintly paranoid (Bradley Coopers nervy, obnoxious performance recalls Alfred Molinas coked-out millionaire in Boogie Nights, minus the sense of lethal threat). With its sweaty, hothouse color palette and sculptural use of natural California light and haze (the cinematography is credited to Anderson and Michael Bauman), it feels as if the breathtaking, tactile flashback in Inherent Vice when Joaquin Phoenix and Katherine Waterston make out in the rain to Neil Youngs Journey Through the Past has been extended to two hours. And after the masterful but claustrophobic chamber drama of Phantom Thread, the loose, playful vibe suggests a filmmaker enjoying being able to make work fully on his own terms. Adam Nayman

shows.title: Slow Horses
shows.writeup: Slow Horses is everything you could possibly want in a TV show: espionage, smoke and mirrors, dry British wit, office humor, endless dysfunction, and lived-in performances from Gary Oldman on down. Think of it as Tinker Tailor Soldier Spy by way of The Thick of It. Andrew Gruttadaro

House of the Dragon has what many fans were most enraptured by in the early seasons of Game of Thrones. Theres intense palace intrigue, duplicitous characters, complex and ever-shifting alliances, and many shades of gray. There is a lot of violence and a lot of dragons. And, crucially, there is a book that details the entire storywith an ending and everything. Andand!the guy who made the entire world is intimately involved, just like he was in the first few seasons of Thrones. Riley McAtee
shows.title: House of the Dragon
Squid Game
shows.writeup: There is no way to describe the premise of Squid Game without sounding like you ate Tide Pods for breakfast. The series, which was written and directed by Hwang Dong-hyuk, tells the story of a deadbeat dad with a gambling addiction named Seong Gi-hun. Gi-hun owes a small fortune to the bank, and another small fortune to a bookie whose gang comes around to rough him up. He has a 10-year-old daughter, and he loves her, but he doesnt get to see her much, and when he does see her, he cant seem to help letting her down. One night, in a subway station, Gi-hun meets a strange man in a suit who makes him a proposition. Lets play ddakji, he says, referring to a game in which one player throws a folded paper at another paper belonging to the second player, trying to flip it over. If Gi-hun wins, the stranger promises to give him 100,000 won; if he loses, Gi-hun has to give the stranger the same amount or let the stranger slap him in the face. After a long and degrading scene, the stranger gives the newly red-cheeked Gi-hun a card with a phone number on it. He says: Call that number if you want to play a game for higher stakes. Brian Phillips

In the 20-plus years since its release, The Talented Mr. Ripley, a movie about looks and reflections, remains one of our best-looking contemporary films. Anthony Minghellas adaptation of the 1955 Patricia Highsmith novel is concerned with surfaces and the depths they conceal. This Ripley is a movie about the intimacy of objects. Visually, the film remains stunning for its lush evocation of depravity concealed by good manners and better clothes; texturally, the depth of feeling is as enduring as the bloodstain that wont wash off. Haley Mlotek
shows.title: The Talented Mr. Ripley

shows.writeup: I had S.S. Rajamoulis previous Telugu-language blockbuster, Eega, on my list of the best foreign-language films of the 2010s, and RRR is even more rousing and accessible: an epic period drama about two Indian revolutionariesmythic stand-ins for real-life figuresbattling the British Raj in 1920. Verisimilitude isnt really Rajamoulis thing: Hes a purveyor of broad, stylized, seriocomic chaos, a gifted and unpretentious hybrid of Baz Luhrmann and James Cameron who puts showmanship first. And he should, because hes a really great showman. The movies two big set piecesa turbo-charged ensemble dance number and a fiery siege featuring a menagerie of lethal CGI animalsare so much more choreographically sophisticated than anything Marvel has produced that they seem to belong to another medium. At three hours, RRRs relentless pacing and endless narrative reversals can feel punishing, but the overall effect is exhilarating. Whens the last time a big-budget action movie felt like too much of a good thing? Adam Nayman
shows.title: RRR
Billions
shows.writeup: The bar for second-season improvements has been set so high in recent years its easy to miss the shows that coast just underneath. Billions was one of those shows that slipped under the radar. The Showtime drama didnt reinvent the wheel in its second season, but there was something different about the tale of U.S. Attorney Chuck Rhoades (Paul Giamatti) and his great white insider trading whale Bobby Axelrod (Damian Lewis) this year. It became more fun. It became more focused. It became just better. Alison Herman

shows.title: Pitch Perfect
shows.writeup: Above all else, Pitch Perfect perfectly captures what a wild and fun comedy adventure with a huge dose of singing can do for the soul. Anna Kendrick stars as Beca, a college freshman who doesnt know where or how to fit in until her bright singing voice shows the way. Beca joins her college a capella group, but quickly realizes that the club is suffocating under the weight of tradition and routine. A catalyst in her own right, she finds a way to turn everything around for the Barden Bellasbut not without a few speed bumps. Pitch Perfect is a testament to the joy of breaking the mold. And with complementary performances from comedy experts like Rebel Wilson, Adam Devine, and Elizabeth Banks, and more than enough head-bopping songs, its also a joy to watch. Jordan Latimore

Admittedly, many prior video game adaptations that werent as well tailored to TV to begin with have fallen prey to such self-sabotage. But the latest and greatest attempt to successfully translate a game to another on-screen medium sidestepped every potential pitfall, just like Joel and Ellie silently sneaking around one of the games (and shows) fungal monstrosities. The criticaland soon, almost certainly, popularacclaim generated by HBOs The Last of Us should establish beyond any doubt that a live-action adaptation of a video game can be an award winner and a huge hit, announcing to an industry thats already all-in on video game intellectual property that the so-called curse of video game movies and shows has been lifted. Ben Lindbergh

The Last of Us premieres on Sunday, January 15.
shows.title: The Last of Us

shows.writeup: The series is the most sustained exploration of Quinn outside of Margot Robbies live-action portrayalwhich, through no fault of the actress, didnt go great on David Ayers Suicide Squad. And while there are legitimately heartfelt moments in the show, its biggest selling point is, quite simply, how hilarious it is. The series version of Bane is just one extended punch line aimed at Tom Hardys Sean Connery crossed with a sleep apnea machine voice and overall approach to the character in The Dark Knight Risesa recurring bit that only gets funnier the longer its drawn out. Harley Quinn marches to the beat of its own drum, but in doing so, it pushes boundaries that are rarely crossed in live-action DC adaptations. Miles Surrey
shows.title: Harley Quinn

shows.writeup: Min Jin Lees sprawling novel Pachinko is a multigenerational epic that follows a single familys journey from occupied Korea to postwar Japan. Its adaptation, a limited series on Apple TV+ spearheaded by The Terrors Soo Hugh, puts its own inventive twist on Lees structure, reshaping the story for TV while amplifying its themes. Rather than a single, linear narrative that moves forward through time, this version of Pachinko juxtaposes two timelines: one in which a young woman named Sunja (Minha Kim) must cross an ocean to provide for her family, and another in which her grandson Solomon (Jin Ha) attempts to assimilate by working for a prestigious Japanese bank. Combined with the best opening credits sequence this side of The Sopranos, Pachinko proves itself an exceptional entry in the literary-hit-to-prestige-miniseries pipeline. The tears will flow, and every one is earned. Alison Herman
shows.title: Pachinko
The James Bond Collection
shows.writeup:
For a while, Prime had what you needed if you craved a martinishaken, not stirredin any era, consumed by whichever James Bond you preferred. Unfortunately thats about to end: Roger Moore, Sean Connery, Timothy Dalton, and Pierce Brosnan will all be departing the service soon, leaving behind only vestiges of Daniel Craigs contributions to the canon (Skyfall and No Time to Die are hanging behind). Its gonna be a long time before theres a new James Bond, so you might wanna indulge in the old ones while you can. Andrew Gruttadaro

The James Bond Collection is leaving Prime Video on Nov. 4.

An Upper East Sider, a comedy nerd, an elite athlete, and an earnest bookworm walk into a dorm suite and immediately become best friends forever, despite having no discernible commonality or overlapping interests (except, of course, sex). So goes the real-life college experience, as well as the circumstances for The Sex Lives of College Girls four bumbling freshman roommates. Like watching the origin story to how the girls in Girls could have ever possibly become friends, Justin Noble and Mindy Kalings foray into college dorm life is, joke-for-joke, one of the funniest shows on TV. In Season 2, Leighton, Bela, Whitney, and Kimberly have returned from Thanksgiving break more confident, more ambitious, and more socially, sexually, and charmingly disastrous than ever. Oh, to be young (and written by Mindy Kaling) again. Jodi Walker
shows.title: The Sex Lives of College Girls
Hustle
shows.writeup: Adam Sandler has found a surprising new niche: movies in which he acts alongside NBA power forwards featuring scenes at Celtics-Sixers games. In 2019, Sandler starred in Uncut Gems, an anxiety roller coaster that featured a scene-stealing performance from Kevin Garnett and revolved around a series of (ill-advised) bets on a Boston-Philly playoff series. In his new movie, Hustle, Sandlers NBA costar is Jazz reserve Juancho Hernangmez, and the movie wraps with a scene at a Celtics-Sixers game that seems to be a season opener, or perhaps a preseason game. The stakes are lower this time around. Hustle is not the first movie with a streets-to-spotlight story of an overlooked athlete. It takes place almost entirely in Philadelphia and features a seven-minute training montage in which Hernangmezs character runs up a staircase and celebrates. Its been done before. But Hustle will be particularly entertaining for die-hard NBA fans, due to its sheer immersion in the NBA world. I counted 29 active or former NBA players in the credits, plus dozens of appearances from coaches, media personalities, front office members, team owners, and more. Rodger Sherman

shows.title: Reservation Dogs
shows.writeup: The first season of Reservation Dogs ends with a dream deferred. Throughout the FX comedys first season, its namesake crew has set its sights on California, a fantasy solution to some very real problems. Every scheme, from stealing a truck full of potato chips to hawking meat pies outside a health clinic, was supposed to save money for the foursomes fresh start, far from the Muscogee reservation they call home. But by the end of the eighth and final episode, only Elora Danan (Devery Jacobs)the groups most harshly pragmatic member, named after the character from Willowhas made her escape. Cheese (Lane Factor) and Willie Jack (Paulina Alexis) have chosen to stay; Bear (DPharaoh Woon-A-Tai) was ready to go, only for Elora to leave him behind. Shes partnered up with the leader of a rival group instead, correctly sensing a kindred spirit beneath the meaningless turf war. Alison Herman

shows.title: Road House
shows.writeup: The 1989 Patrick Swayzestarring film Road House isnt a movie so much as it is a religious experience, and one that defines the Good Bad Movies genre. There may have been terribly awesome films before it, but as far as Im concerned, Road House invented the concept and is the standard by which every other Good Bad Movie should be judged. Mark Titus

shows.title: Sorry to Bother You
shows.writeup: Sorry to Bother You, the directorial debut from rapper Boots Riley, is a weird movie. Whenever its main character, a telemarketer (the great LaKeith Stanfield), calls someone, his desk is transported into the room with them (its not really happening, but it is an undeniably unique, bizarre visual flourish); the telemarketers artist girlfriend, Detroit (Tessa Thompson), does a performance in which the audience throws old cellphones, bullet casings, and balloons filled with lambs blood at her while she recites dialogue from The Last Dragon; and then, with about 20 minutes until the end of a movie, a naked horse-person falls out of a bathroom stall. Im seriousor at least I think I am; it feels entirely possible that this was all a fever dream.Thats how jarring, horrifying, and darkly comical the ending of Sorry to Bother You is, a sequence of events that amplifies the surreal feeling of an already disconcertingly surreal movie. It is bizarre and unforgettable, and completely unexpected. Miles Surrey

No less of an iconoclast than D.H. Lawrence famously opined about the necessity of trusting the tale rather than the teller, which makes Trs slight untrustworthiness as a movie about these very issues hard to gauge. Is Todd Field a reactionary apologist working in bad faith to exacerbate woke culture, or is the ultimate ignominy of his protagonists fate his way of suggesting that for geniuses no less than the rest of us, the moral arc of the universe bends toward poetic justice? We need a new narrative, an image consultant tells Lydia Tr somewhere in the homestretch, and our last glimpse of her, broken but unbowed, feels right precisely because it gives the lie to that statement. You cant separate the art from the artist, but you can change the venue. Adam Nayman

Streaming now on VOD.
shows.title: Tr
Copenhagen Cowboy
shows.writeup: At just six episodes, all of which run under an hour, Copenhagen Cowboy should be more accessibleand presumably far cheaper to producethan Nicolas Winding Refns grand Amazon experiment, Too Old to Die Young. The show is also something of a homecoming for the director, who filmed in his native Denmark for the first time since wrapping up his Pusher trilogy in 2005. Still, for better or for worse, Copenhagen Cowboy finds Refn continuing to double down on the thematic interests and languid pacing that have pulled the auteur further from the mainstream since he broke out with Drive. Miles Surrey

shows.title: What If...?
shows.writeup: True to its title, What If? explores the many other realities that could have been lived by members of the MCU. The second episode, "What If... T'Challa Became a Star-Lord?" ponders a path in which TChalla doesnt become the Black Panther. Its a fascinating and vivid journey, but What If? is also notable for more tragic reasons: Its the last time that Chadwick Boseman played the character.
This glass-blowing competition series goes to show you that anything can be turned into bingeable reality content. Literally anything.
shows.title: Blown Away

shows.writeup: As a sports origin story, King Richard thankfully avoids giving away precious tennis tips and instead focuses on the various kinds of nurturing that the girls received. In this very approbatory film, Richard never chooses between being his daughters father or their coach. He remains both, and makes sure they can be at once little girls and future champions. The family, and all the support it represents, isnt an empty tradition for him, but the very soil from which happiness and freedom can grow. Mani Lazic
shows.title: King Richard

shows.writeup: The kick-ass prequel the Predator franchise deserves, elegantly told from the perspective of a Comanche girl from the Northern Great Plains on a journey from being hunted to the hunter.
shows.title: Prey

shows.writeup: For this season, returning castaways are brought to the islands of Micronesia to compete against Survivor superfans. Its a physically brutal season (the first to have TWO medical evacuations!) that benefits from strong women and easily manipulated men. The Black Widow Brigade is one of the bestif not the bestSurvivor alliances ever, and their run toward the end of this season is historic, iconic, and a compelling argument for why women should always stick together. (Also streaming on Netflix.)
shows.title: Survivor: Micronesia

shows.writeup: In Paul Schraders 1980 flick about a male sex worker who ends up framed for murder after a high-profile rendezvous, Richard Gere played the titular character, sporting a suave haircut and suits that looked both cheap and iconic. In Showtimes TV adaptation, premiering on Sept. 11, Jon Bernthal steps into those same suits, and finds himself caught in the middle of a similar conspiracy. Reviews have been iffy, with many calling the show sleazy. But when youre hitting play on a series starring Bernthal thats called American Gigoloisnt sleaze what youre looking for? Andrew Gruttadaro
shows.title: American Gigolo

shows.writeup: In this Irish comedy/thriller/murder mystery, the Garvey clan is brought back together by the premature death of their parents. Thats a bit of a bleak loglineany time youre putting comedy and murder in the same sentence youre walking a thin line. But Bad Sisters is helmed by Sharon Horgan, a dependable comedic mind and one of the creators of the brilliant and underrated Catastrophe. If theres anyone who can pull this off, its her. Plus, the show comes with yet another magnetic performance from Claes Bang, fresh off some naked sword-fighting in The Northman. Andrew Gruttadaro
shows.title: Bad Sisters
Cyberpunk: Edgerunners
shows.writeup: Cyberpunk: Edgerunners pulled off the content heist of the year. The Netflix series is an anime based on IP from a 2020 action role-playing game that had such a disastrous, bug-filled launch that the games developer, CD Projekt Red, issued refunds and a statement asking for fans to give us a chance. In the popular consciousness, Cyberpunk 2077 was left for dead. Then Hiroyuki Imaishi (Gurren Lagann, Kill la Kill) and his team at Studio Trigger resurrected that radioactive corpse through the sheer blunt force trauma of their overwhelming style. Edgerunners is a neon monument to the power of creating something so saturated with visual flair that it becomes undeniable. The show takes the hallmarks of Studio Trigger projectsfluid motion, anarchic energy, relentless horniness, fantastic if nonsensical plotsand adds a layer of piercing distortion to the mix. Through 10 episodes, Imaishi and his creative team helm a loose adaptation of a society that has fully integrated technology into biological life at the expense of their humanity. The result is a show so beautiful and immediate that its goodwill has trickled down to the game its based on, helping it cross 20 million copies sold and forcing one of its directors to emotionally admit that its fucking good to be back. Charles Holmes

shows.title: The Social Network
shows.writeup: The Social Network is stamped into Facebooks DNA. As Steven Levy describes in the first chapter of Facebook: The Inside Story, Zuckerberg is asked about the movie in places as far-flung as Nigeria. In 2018, The New Yorker reported that Facebook executives still refer to The Social Network resentfully as the movie. From its facts to its essence to its portrayal, I think that was a very unfair picture, Facebook COO Sheryl Sandberg said in the same piece. I still think it forms the basis of a lot of what people believe about Mark. Alyssa Bereznak

shows.title: The Real Housewives of Beverly Hills
shows.writeup: If You Can Watch Only One Season: Check out the first season, when Faye Resnick and Camille Grammer square off during the infamous Dinner Party From Hell.

The Kardashian-Jenners are back for a second season, once again giving us a look inside their lives in and out of Calabasas. Two episodes in, weve already delved into the Tristan and Khloe cheating drama, flown off to Milan Fashion Week with Kim and Kendall, and dined with a horny Kourtney and Travis inside their Palm Springs home. With lives so public, its only a matter of time before we bear witness to behind-the-scenes coverage of Kims now-infamous get your fucking ass up and work comments, Kourtneys Dolce & Gabbanasponsored nuptials, and Kendalls (temporary) split with Devin Booker. Amelia Wedemeyer
shows.title: The Kardashians
Floor Is Lava
shows.writeup: Part parkour, part living out your childhood fantasies, this reality competition show lends something rare to our ever-curated streaming culture: broad appeal.

shows.title: Barry
shows.writeup: Killing for hire and show business seems like an odd pairing, but Barry has expertly wedded these professions and the self-delusion required to navigate them successfully. Whether its a hitman with a history of turning to violence to solve all his problems thinking he can be absolved of his sins or a showrunner charging along with a series that stretches the truth of her history with abuse, Barry continues to shine a light on damaged characters who refuse to look at themselves in the mirror. The results havent been pretty going into Season 3, but as is true to Tinseltown, the show must go on. Miles Surrey

shows.title: The Dark Knight
shows.writeup: Heat with capes; the best superhero movie ever made because its not a superhero movie. Christopher Nolan used Batman as a Trojan horse to bring an epic, urban crime drama into the multiplex. It also helps that it features the single best performance found in any superhero movie. Chris Ryan

shows.title: Mythic Quest
shows.writeup: Mythic Quest doesnt succeed because it accurately documents daily life at a game studio. In gaming, what matters more than anything is whether the finished product is fun. In comedy, what matters more than anything is whether its funny. Mythic Quest is funny, deliciously satirical and, at times, touching. Its probably the best live-action TV series ever made about video games, but at its core, its a workplace comedy where the workplace is new but the comedy is time-tested. Ben Lindbergh

shows.title: Elvis
shows.writeup: Austin Butler is at his best when he plays against the limits of Elviss intelligence, or at least the limits of his sophistication. In a scene late in the movie, he visits Colonel Tom Parker in a hospital room, planning to fire his manager for good. But when presented with a business proposition that is at best mildly enticing, doubt creeps across Elviss face: Butler plays personal guilt and ugly ambition in equal measure, his Elvis a gentle person saddled with insatiable appetites. Paul Thompson

With an initial setup of two strangers accidentally double-booked at an Airbnb in a dilapidated Detroit neighborhood, Barbarian seems like a by-the-numbers thriller until one of the characters discovers a hidden passageway in the rentals basement. From there, Barbarian emerges as a worthy successor to James Wans Malignant for the title of WTF Studio Movie of the Year. And just like Malignants Gabriel, a parasitic twin living on the back of a womans skull who can take control of her body, the true star of Barbarian is a memorable monstrosity that is sure to generate discussion and dank memes. Miles Surrey
shows.title: Barbarian
Everything Everywhere All At Once
shows.writeup: In one of the many martial arts showdowns that punctuate Everything Everywhere All at Once, a character adopts an unorthodox fighting stance: As she locks her body into place, her arms remain open wide, as if offering an embrace. Of all the images that one could use to sum up this alternately invigorating and enervating sci-fi action comedy, this may be the most apt. In evaluating Daniel Kwan and Daniel Scheinerts sophomore feature, its nearly impossible to separate pleasure from pain. Watching it is like being brutalized by good vibes, or trying to get a breath in edgewise while a pair of ambitious, well-intentioned filmmakers try to hug you to death. Adam Nayman

The bigger the targetor the vainer the billionairethe easier they are to hit, and if Glass Onion isnt exactly crack-shot satire, it scores enough scattered bulls-eyes to get by. Like its surprise-hit predecessor, it represents a very contemporary attempt by Rian Johnson to thread sardonic socioeconomic critique through well-worn murder-mystery tropes la Agatha Christie. In both films, the revelation of guilt and motive is arguably less important than the ambient send-up of 1-percentersthe same debonair class humor that Christie managed on the page without making such a big deal of it. Adam Nayman
shows.title: Glass Onion: A Knives Out Mystery
Andor
shows.writeup: When Andor begins, about five years before the events of Rogue One and Episode IV, the Empire has consolidated its control of the galaxy. Its not just a dark time for the Rebellion; its a time so dark that theres barely a Rebellion at all. Cassian has been fighting, running, and suffering from the tumult of a war-torn galaxy his whole life. He has little to loseand, crucially, Disney has little to lose by letting him behave in questionable ways, because we already know from Rogue One what kind of man he is, and how and when he dies. Andors days on screen are numbered, as are (by choice) Tony Gilroys as a Star Wars auteur, so the Mouse might as well make the most of them and take what for Disney qualifies as a creative risk. Ben Lindbergh
Taking place in a time frame close to Andor, Rebels includes several characters, like Saw Gerrera, who will appear in Andor.
shows.title: Star Wars Rebels
Blow Out
shows.writeup: The wheels within wheels keep spinning, quite literally, in the celebrated, two-minute-long, 360-degree shot in Blow Out, when the camera simulates a reel of magnetic tape being erased. The tape contains nature recordings gathered by a sound technician (John Travolta, never better) who inadvertently captures a Chappaquiddick that silent assassins want scrubbed. The hypnotic shot is also the closest any filmmaker has come to imagining the world from a turntables point of view. Perhaps the films most vocal advocate, Pauline Kael, once said, Id say among the things I get rapped for the most thats probably number one and number two is my praise of Brian De Palma. James Hughes

shows.title: Welcome to Chippendales
shows.writeup: Before there was Magic Mike and its lucrative live show, there was Chippendales. The franchise still exists to this day, but the male burlesque has long been a pop cultural punch line; its more likely you first saw the signature uniformbow ties over bare chestson SNL than onstage. This aura obscures the genuine subversion of the Chippendales concept, which got slightly more respect when attached to an auteur like Steven Soderbergh. (A strip club where women objectify men? Better to laugh it off than think too hard about their wants and needs!) Its also overshadowed the sordid story behind the striptease: the 1987 murder of Nick De Noia, Chippendales choreographer and chief creative force, at the behest of founder Somen Steve Banerjee. Alison Herman

The Bad Batch is both brand new and older in origin than most recent or scheduled Star Wars releases. Its designed to stand on its own, but it owes deep debts in appearance, content, and tone to the predecessor that spawned it, The Clone Wars. And although it lays claim to a time period unexplored by previous Star Wars movies and TV shows, its also hemmed in by the inviolable narratives of two trilogies. All of that makes The Bad Batch harder to hype, and perhaps harder to sell to casual fans and those who havent fallen for the earlier animated shows. But ultimately, The Bad Batch extends a strong run of small-screen series created or produced by Dave Filoni, a protg of George Lucas whose inspired Star Wars work has helped tie together the 44-year-old franchises pre- and post-Disney trilogies and timelines. Ben Lindbergh
shows.title: Star Wars: The Bad Batch
The Lego Star Wars Holiday Special
shows.writeup: What's better than the live-action Star Wars Holiday Special? A Lego version, featuring all corners of the Star Wars universe and time travel! Combining the wackiness of the Lego animated features with Star Wars creates the perfect event for the entire family. While the voices might sound a little off, the special will have enough winks and nods for even the most diehard fans, with enough zip and pop for the casuals. Arjuna Ramgopal

Its not as taboo as the title might implythis new Netflix dating series pairs single siblings together as they help each other find their perfect match, and maybe win $100,000 in the process. OK, thats still pretty weird.
shows.title: Dated and Related

shows.writeup: Jennifer Lawrence built her career on embodying a classical kind of heroine. At the beginning of Causeway, however, Lawrence doesnt display her now-trademark idea of strength. We meet Lynsey (Lawrence) as she enters a rehab center after her time in the military. She goes through a series of physical exercises to try to regain control of her body after suffering brain damage during an attack in Afghanistan, relearning basic coordination skills and the ability to walk unaided. Shes clearly resentful of the situation, having to rely on a nurse to go to the bathroom or drive. Yet theres no self-pity in Lawrences performance. The hurt and the shame are tangible, but so is the tendency toward self-preservation and isolation. Throughout the movie, first-time feature director Lila Neugebauer avoids pathos and instead focuses on the brutal reality of rehabilitation, the hopes dashed by relapses, and the terror of being betrayed by ones own body. Mani Lazic
shows.title: Causeway

shows.writeup: When Love Is Blind launched the day before Valentines Day 2020, it was easy to dismiss as a gimmick: an unofficial companion piece to The Circle, and another attempt by Netflix to cement its foothold in the reality TV space. But just because a show has a gimmick doesnt mean it wont make for entertaining television. In fact, Love Is Blind had two gimmicks, difficult to explain but irresistible to watch: First, contestants spent 16-hour days in isolated chambers known as pods, choosing a partner to marry without ever interacting face-to-face. Then, couples were fast-tracked from engagement to wedding ceremony in a period of weeks, hitting traditional roadblocks like family introductions and moving in while still adjusting to the physical reality of each others existence. And everyone knows what happens when a moving car hits a bump in the road at full speed. Alison Herman
shows.title: Love Is Blind
Casino
shows.writeup: When you love someone you gotta trust em theres no other way. So says Sam Ace Rothstein (Robert De Niro) in the opening moments of Casino, outlining a worldview that would seem to be at odds with his status as Las Vegass reigning bettor extraordinaire. In gambling, love and trust are dicey propositions; most of the time, youre better off relying on blind chance. Adam Nayman

The world is changed, Cate Blanchetts Galadriel said in the prologue of The Lord of the Rings: The Fellowship of the Ring. I feel it in the water. I feel it in the earth. I smell it in the air. Twenty-one years later, Amazons mega-expensive series set within J.R.R. Tolkiens Middle Earth is imminentnot unlike a certain dark sorcerers rise to power. Fans of the books and the movies have been waiting years for a return to the beloved fantasy world, but The Lord of the Rings: The Rings of Power might not be what theyre expecting. Emma Stefansky
shows.title: The Rings of Power
Abbott Elementary
shows.writeup: A workplace comedy set in a Philadelphia public school, Abbott Elementary features a slew of charming child actors as its namesakes rambunctious student body. (One of the shows many triumphs is how it mines the kids behavior for laughs without mocking them.) But its core cast are the teachers, who form a flawlessly balanced ensemble. Quinta Brunson plays Janine, a relative rookie as earnest as she is inexperienced. The part is an effective showcase, but compared to her costars, its clear Brunson had the savvy and lack of ego to cast herself as the straight woman. Sheryl Lee Ralph shines as Barbara, a seasoned pro intimidating in her efficacy, while Janelle James is the breakout as Ava, the deliciously incompetent principal. Abbott Elementary is neither saccharine nor cynical in its treatment of systemic issues, an impressive balancing act thats actually earned the acclaim it deserves. Alison Herman

shows.title: Ahed's Knee
shows.writeup: A self-reflexive, explosive portrait of a filmmaker battling censorship from the gifted Israeli filmmaker Nada Lapid.

Dark was one of the most surprising series of the past 10 years, as well as proof that Netflixs foray into international productions could be successful stateside. Its labyrinthine, time-traveling mystery was deeply engrossing and its performances were bracingly captivating; its esoteric nature was part of the appeal. Now comes 1899, the latest series from the minds of Darks creators, Jantje Friese and Baran bo Odar. The story follows a ship full of passengers who encounter unexplainable circumstances while crossing the Atlantic Ocean. But thats just what we know right nowthe true joy of this series will be discovering what lies at the bottom of the sea. Andrew Gruttadaro

shows.title: Euphoria
shows.writeup: Euphoria has always been a bumpy ride, both for viewers and, according to some recent reports, behind the scenes. (The role of Barbie Ferreiras character Kat Hernandez has been noticeably diminished in Season 2. According to The Daily Beast, Ferreira walked off set multiple times during production following disputes with Sam Levinson and did not attend the season premiere.) Euphoria is a disorienting mix of genres, tones, stakes, and overall vibes, a whiplash-inducing experience thats chaotic by design. The show as a whole is narrated by Rue, who serves as our Virgil through the raging inferno of teen angst. But the end of Season 2 ups the ante even further: In the world of Euphoria, the stage play that takes up much of the seasons final two episodes is narrated, written, and directed by an actual teenager. As always, Euphorias excesses are a lot more endearingwhich is to say, less exhaustingwhen theyre canonically rooted in enthusiastic immaturity. Alison Herman

Steven Spielberg waited nearly 20 years to make an official war film in the form of Saving Private Ryanwhich, true to Spielbergs MO, was made to be the ultimate movie of its kind. Its innovation was to restage D-Day imagery familiar to millions from movies, television shows, and documentaries but punctuated with horror and gore the likes of which had not really been attempted. To see a filmmaker who made his fortune peddling exhilarating escapism suddenly entrap viewers in a relentless, chaotic, multidirectional nightmare was an undeniable show of power. Adam Nayman
shows.title: Saving Private Ryan
The Righteous Gemstones
shows.writeup: The Righteous Gemstones is a comedy that used the premise of an over-the-top family of televangelists as an entry point and then spent its first season delving into family drama thatd make any prestige series blushdebauchery, blackmail, endless in-fighting. With a cast that includes Walton Goggins, Adam Devine, and a scene-stealing Edi Patterson in addition to John Goodman and Danny McBride, Season 1 painted a picture of a family so busy lining their own pockets that they lost their way. Now, Season 2 plans to go even deeper, exploring Eli Gemstones past and how it led him to becoming a megachurch mogul. Alan Siegel

Otherwise known as The One Featuring Every MCU Superhero Ever. But because TChalla oversees a nation whose technology far outpaces any other on planet Earth, he and his people are hugely important in the movies central conflict against the genocidal Thanos. (And in a moment that connects Infinity War to Civil War, Steve Rogers visits the country to retrieve his best buddy, Bucky.) The climactic battle, in which Wakandan forces skirmish against Thanoss army, is one of the franchises best.
shows.title: Avengers: Infinity War

shows.writeup: The log line for this manga series should be enough of a selling point here: An impoverished young man makes a deal that fuses his body with a dog-like devil that allows him to turn parts of his body into chainsaws. (The title, as it turns out, is quite literal.) But beyond the awesome gnarliness of that, theres the fact that Chainsaw Man comes from the esteemed mind of Tatsuki Fujimoto and was produced by one of the best Japanese animation studios in MAPPA. Chainsaw Man might not be the first thing you click on, but it could be the best. Andrew Gruttadaro
shows.title: Chainsaw Man

shows.writeup: Captain Riker once asserted that the ship will clean itself, and maybe the biomatter resequencers or janitorial robots can erase some stains. In Lower Decks, however, we learn that unlucky ensigns are assigned to holodeck waste removal. In the words of Ensign Mariner, the skilled but unambitious and rebellious ex-officer voiced by Tawny Newsome, If Id known I was going to be emptying the holodeck biofilters, I wouldnt have had so much for breakfast. These days, relatively little is off limits for Star Trek, including cleaning up the residue of a sensual stardate. I think Star Trek can be many, many, many things, says creator Mike McMahan. Ben Lindbergh
shows.title: Star Trek: Lower Decks
The Banshees of Inisherin
shows.writeup: This feeling of performers as perfectly matched opponents has only gotten richer and deeper 15 years later in Martin McDonaghs latest drama, The Banshees of Inisherin, which reteams Colin Farrell and Brendan Gleeson to superlative effect. The filmset in the Aran Islands during 1923, amid the waning days of the Irish Civil Wargot a 15-minute standing ovation in Venice and looks set to be a fall-season awards contender. (I tried to leave at the seventh minute, joked Farrell to Stephen Colbert.) Like In Bruges, its an ornery study of masculine rituals and psychology that also doubles as a meditation on purgatory; the difference is that where In Brugess antiheroes were effectively rubberneckers in a foreign cityRay, you are about the worst tourist in the worldthe characters in Banshees have all but merged with their home turf. Theyre as much a part of the landscape as the fields and the cliffs. Neither aging musician Colm (Gleeson), who lives alone in a large house on the shoreline, nor cheery dairy farmer Pdraic (Farrell), whos situated farther uphill with sister Siobhn (Kerry Condon), harbor illusions about ever leaving Inisherinalive or dead. What begins to drive a wedge in the pairs long-standing friendship are their differing philosophies on what to do with the time they have left there in the great in-betweeny. Adam Nayman

Scott Pilgrim vs. the World premiered on August 13, 2010, and quickly evolved from box office flop to sneaky cult classic to widely acknowledged masterpiece. Edgar Wrights relentless hybrid action-comedyits a kung-fu flick, its superhero adjacent, its a punk-rock musical, its a (post-)teen romance, its a shrewd skewering of both dopey toxic masculinity and the very notion of a Manic Pixie Dream Girlwas so far ahead of its time as to render its time irrelevant entirely. Rob Harvilla
shows.title: Scott Pilgrim vs. the World

shows.writeup: The first weeks of January are a time for experimentation. Theyre a time for sentient murder-dolls, and a time for heist shows that can be watched in whatever order the viewer chooses. Netflix has dabbled in the choose-your-own-adventure format before, and with Kaleidoscope its doing it again, structuring the episodes of a heist story starring Giancarlo Esposito, Rufus Sewell, Paz Vega, and more so that they can be watched as you see fit. The streamers already laid out a guide to the different paths one can take, but ultimately its up to you. Whether this makes Kaleidoscope a good TV show is up for debate. But its at least exciting to try something new, isnt it? Andrew Gruttadaro
shows.title: Kaleidoscope
Planes, Trains and Automobiles
shows.writeup: Traveling the week of Thanksgiving is the worst. Everyone knows that. And everyone probably knows that because of Planes, Trains and Automobiles, the John Hughes classic in which Steve Martin and John Candy submit dueling MVP performances as two odd-couple travelers trying to make it home in time for the holidays. Its an undeniable classic, a showcase of two comedic actors going off, and the only movie that encapsulates how the hell-on-earth experience of overcrowded airports and bus depots all becomes worth it once youre at the family dinner table. Andrew Gruttadaro

The Favourite may have earned The Great its series order in 2019, but it predates Tony McNamaras work with Yorgos Lanthimosthe pilot script actually got McNamara the job from a crowded field of 150 contenders. The subject matter of The Great is an even more natural fit for the projects shared themes: In a Russia left behind by the Enlightenment, a situation Catherine would eventually work to alleviate, the extravagance of an imperial court really was play-acting at European sophistication, all while serfs lived in human bondage and education was scarce. Alison Herman
shows.title: The Great
Atlanta
shows.writeup: When Atlanta emerged in the fall of 2016, it made an immediate dent in the cultural stratosphere in a way very few shows can ever hope to achieve. The brainchild of polymath comedian, musician, and writer Donald Glover along with his creative team, Atlanta was a perfect storm: a Southern Gothic drama, a hyperspecific regional portrait of the current capital of hip-hop, a vision of Twin Peaksian offbeat humor about the Black experience, and maybe most importantly, a brilliantly casted and unquestionably hip version of the American sitcom. The series premiered with two episodes, which helped to properly contextualize the kind of show it wanted to be: There was an introductory pilot establishing the people and place involved, and then an outlandish second episode that took a strange, sometimes horrific, sometimes absurd detour into the prison system. Beyond just being a memorable hour of television, it established the dark, enigmatic, and surrealistic tone of the series. It could be anything at any time. Israel Daramola

shows.title: The Crown
shows.writeup: Over time, its become clear that The Crown is a show built for the long haul, growing into its golden years as Queen Elizabeth ages into her own authority. In retrospect, Season 1s weaknesses are more understandable: The Crowns story simply hadnt caught up to The Crowns true interests, both historic and thematic. That slow burn could be frustrating. Its also evidence of a patience and long-term thinking thats at once unique to television and increasingly rare to find within it. As Princess Dianas and Margaret Thatchers twin meteors make their crash landing, that patience is finally paying off. Alison Herman

shows.title: Draft Day
shows.writeup: Draft Day is a movie about Kevin Costner trying to SAVE FOOTBALL IN CLEVELAND. He plays Sonny Weaver, the GM of the Browns, who own the seventh pick in the 2014 NFL draft. Hes looking at Vontae Mack, a linebacker out of Ohio State who has a big mouth on Twitter, and Ray Jennings, a running back out of Florida State who, in a first for any athlete ever, tells his dad, I just want to be a Brown. But the Browns owner (a how-did-I-get-here Frank Langella) wants Weaver to make a splash in the draft, and hes infatuated with Bo Callahan, a quarterback widely expected to go no. 1 overall. And why wouldnt he want him? A linebacker or a running back cant SAVE FOOTBALL IN CLEVELAND. So when Seahawks GM Tom Michaels (Patrick St. Esprit) lays out a deal that would give Cleveland the no. 1 pick, its Weavers chance to you guessed it: SAVE FOOTBALL IN CLEVELAND. By the end of the movie, Weavers made three deals and numerous other decisions. But did he SAVE FOOTBALL IN CLEVELAND? Riley McAtee

shows.title: Hawkeye
shows.writeup: In Hawkeye, the third MCU TV show to be set after the events of Endgame, Clint Barton (Jeremy Renner) faces the consequences of his time as Ronin. Thanks to a talented young archer named Kate Bishop (Hailee Steinfeld), an overzealous fan who decides to fight crime in New York while wearing the same black-and-gold Ronin suit, Clints Christmas plans are interrupted and hes pulled back into superhero life. Together, this new duo of archers is forced to take on the citys criminal underworld, with Clints only wish being to make it back in time for the holiday with his familywho were resurrected by the Blip. Daniel Chin

From the moment John Wick was released, it seemed to inspire a cultlike fascination. The movies instant greatness and ardent fandom wasnt indebted to any one thing, but rather to a combination of its eccentricities, from the stunningly choreographed fight scenes to the revenge tale that hinged on avenging a puppy, the rules-obsessed assassin hotel overseen by Ian McShane, and the stoic charisma of its star, Keanu Reeves. Miles Surrey
shows.title: John Wick

shows.writeup: The legacy of Blade II, and Blade before it, is not often discussed, but its easy to see it as a watershed movie for two since-exploded genres: comic book and vampire movies. The Marvel Cinematic Universe had not yet been established when it came out, as Hollywood was still gauging peoples appetite for the stuff. We also did not yet have Twilight or True Blood, and vampires were largely understood as tortured Victorian heroes, as Blade II director Guillermo del Toro called them. His vision contributed to the conversion of the mythological creatures into the subject of a more postmodern storytelling funhouse (see: What We Do in the Shadows), and was also the biggest hit of his filmmaking career, then a decade old. Blade II was the series most successful entry at the box office, granting del Toro both the berth for more auteurist, award-devouring fare like Pans Labyrinth and The Shape of Water and the keys to other big IP franchises like Pacific Rim and the Ron Perlmanstarring Hellboy (the author of the Hellboy comics, Mike Mignola, served as a concept artist for Blade II). John Wilmes
shows.title: Blade II

shows.writeup: Otherwise known as The One Featuring Every MCU Superhero Ever, Pt. 2. TChalla was one of the many to get wiped out by Thanoss Snap in Infinity War, and thus hes not present for much of Endgame. But make no mistake: He and his Wakandan brethren are essential to the closing chapter of this epic saga.
shows.title: Avengers: Endgame

shows.writeup: In 2004, four years before Taken reintroduced modern film audiences to the concept of middle-aged men wielding a very particular set of skills for the purposes of revenge, Denzel was hunting kidnappers through the streets of Mexico City in Man on Fire. Mr. Washington plays John Creasy, a depressed and down-on-his-heels former special forces operative who is reduced to bodyguarding for a wealthy, very possibly drug-connected family. Their precocious young daughter, Pita (Dakota Fanning), touches Creasys ruined heart, pulling him out of his shell. So, of course, because every middle-aged-man revenge tale needs a precipitating incident usually involving the death, violation, or abduction of a wife, daughter, or daughter figure, shes eventually kidnapped. Creasy goes on a fire-and-brimstone mission of wanton but very focused destruction, tearing the kidnapping cartel down piece by piece, setting fire to a dance club, torturing informants, shooting rocket-propelled grenades in suburban neighborhoods, and putting an explosive pen in a dudes butt.
